Former Orlando Pirates, Lamontville Golden Arrows and Maritzburg United  player Bheka Phakathi has died at the age of 43. According to one of his former teams Arrows, Phakathi died in a fatal car accident that happened on Sunday morning. “Lamontville Golden Arrows are deeply saddened by the news of Bheka Phakathi's passing in a fatal vehicle accident this morning. Our thoughts and prayers lie with his family in this tragic time,” the club said. Orlando Pirates, where Phakathi spent close to four years as a player, have also sent their condolences. At the time of his untimely death, Phakathi was coaching ABC Motsepe outfit Umvoti and had just won the ABC Motsepe League.    